# Approach
 Steps of the mergeAlternately function:

Convert input strings word1 and word2 into character arrays arr1 and arr2.
Initialize a new character array merge with a length of arr1.length + arr2.length to hold the merged characters.
Initialize two indices: i for the merge array and j for tracking characters in word2.
Start a loop that iterates until the merge array is filled with characters from both input strings:
a. Check if j is within the bounds of arr1:
If true, assign arr1[j] to merge[i] and increment both i and j.
b. Check if j is within the bounds of arr2:
If true, assign arr2[j] to merge[i] and increment both i and j.
Return a new string created from the merge array using the String constructor.

